**Full job description**

**Entry level Mine Operator roles -- expression of interest to join our
talent pool.**

-   The perfect balance, our roster gives you more time for the things
    that are important in your life and to your family and community

-   Permanent employment which includes attractive salary, annual
    bonuses and a huge range of additional benefits which are designed
    to make your life better

-   Candidates must already have accommodation in Weipa or the
    surrounding communities

**Assessment Centre taking place Thursday 12th March in Weipa**

We have **entry level mining positions** currently available and are
seeking applications from **Local Aboriginal & First Nations people** to
join our business. You will work as part of our Mine Development or
Production team, operating 776D Haul Trucks with further training
available on other machinery over time. Full on-the-job training will be
provided. This is a fantastic opportunity for people with a strong work
ethic, commitment to learning and a 'can do' attitude.

Positions are available at both Northern or Southern Operations, working
either a rotating **4/5/5 day/night** or **7/7 day/night shift roster**,
giving you more time for the things that are important to you outside of
work. We have options to suit your lifestyle and goals, at Andoom
(Northern Operations) you'll be home after each shift and for roles
based at Amrun (Southern Operations) you will stay at our camp during
shift and commute back to Weipa on days off, with an additional
allowance to compensate you for time away from home.

You'll be part of an inclusive team, supported by your Supervisor to
grow and achieve your own personal goals as well as the goals of the
team.

Successful Candidates will enter a job ready pool of Operators, ready to
be placed into vacancies either at Andoom or Amrun.

**What you'll bring**

-   A commitment to the safety of yourself and your team

-   A valid 'C' class driver's license

-   Respect for others and an all-inclusive mindset

-   High degree of ownership and responsibility for the equipment under
    your control

**What we offer**

-   Full on the job training

-   Competitive base salary

-   Various benefits including remote area allowance, Weipa
    accommodation benefit and remote area holiday travel allowance

-   Amrun allowance (for roles based at Amrun)

-   A work environment where safety is always the number one priority

-   A permanent position working directly for Rio Tinto

-   Comprehensive medical benefits including subsidised private health
    insurance for employees and immediate family

-   Attractive share ownership plan

-   Company provided insurance cover

-   Extensive salary sacrifice & salary packaging options

-   Career development & education assistance to further your technical
    or leadership ambitions

-   Ongoing access to family-friendly health and medical wellbeing
    support

-   Leave for all of life's reasons (annual, paid parental, sick leave)

-   Exclusive employee discounts (banking, accommodation, cars, retail
    and more)

We are committed to promoting diversity within Rio Tinto and as a
special measure to we strongly encourage women to apply.

**Where you will be working**

Our Weipa Operations includes two bauxite mines, processing facilities,
ship loaders, an export wharf, two ports, power stations, a rail network
and ferry terminals. Located on the Western Cape York Peninsula in Far
North Queensland, each year the operation produces more than 35 million
tonnes of bauxite.

Our operations are supported by a 1,900-strong workforce---including 30
per cent who are women and 32 per cent Indigenous employees. Activities
include mine operations, maintenance, asset management, ports, cultural
heritage management, and processing facility management.

The development of Amrun mine, which was completed in 2018, will extend
the life of our Weipa bauxite operations by decades to come and
significantly build on our 55-year history on the Western Cape.

**Applications close Sunday 22nd February 2026**

